data.prayer: Father, help the 443 believers in Tébessa to know your commands and to do them.
data.verse: For Ezra had devoted himself to the study and observance of the Law of the Lord, and to teaching its decrees and laws in Israel.

data.location_label: Photo from the state of Tébessa, Algeria
data.section_summary: What people or resources could you pray for in this photo?

data.prayer: Jesus, help the church in the state of Tébessa to not rely on buildings or programs, but on your Spirit and the simple faithfulness of every believer.
Lord, to the people of Tébessa you say, "If you wait for Me, I will work on your behalf."
data.verse: For from of old men have not heard, nor perceived by the ear, neither has the eye seen a God besides you, who works for him who waits for him.

data.prayer: Spirit, awaken the sleepers and call them to repent and be baptized in the state of Tébessa. Set an urgency in their hearts.
data.verse: And now why do you wait? Rise and be baptized and wash away your sins, calling on his name.’

data.prayer: Lord, please remember the Belbali people. you said you wanted worshippers of every tongue and tribe and nation, yet we know of no worshippers among them.
Jesus, raise up prophets and truth speakers in your church in Tébessa, Algeria so that the church can grow in every way into the mature body of you its head.
data.verse: Instead, speaking the truth in love, we will grow to become in every respect the mature body of him who is the head, that is, Christ.

data.prayer: Father, let the threatened of Tébessa, Algeria know that it is better to trust in you than to trust in humans.
data.verse: It is better to take refuge in the Lord than to trust in humans.

data.prayer: Father, see the suffering of your people in the state of Tébessa. Deliver all those who have not forgotten your Word.
data.verse: Look on my suffering and deliver me, for I have not forgotten your law.
